Name: parasitic Ichthyosporea infectious disease
Definition: A parasitic infectious disease that involves parasitic infection by the members of the class Ichthyosporea

Name: parasitic protozoa infectious disease
Definition: A parasitic infectious disease that is caused by parasitic protozoa which are microorganisms classified as unicellular eukaryotes.

Name: parasitic ectoparasitic infectious disease
Definition: A parasitic infectious disease that is caused by organisms that live primarily on the surface of the host.

Name: parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease
Definition: A parasitic infectious disease that occurs when part of the body is infested with parasitic worms such as cestodes

Name: obsolete Hodgkin's lymphoma
Definition: A parasitic infectious disease that occurs when part of the body is infested with parasitic worms such as cestodes
